name: Akcent
comments: The dance/pop band started as a duo with founder Adrian Sina and Ramona Barta. They released a first album in 2000, "Senzatzia". Thereafter Ramona Barta was replaced by Marius Nedelcu, Mihai Gruia and Sorin Brotnei, resulting in a 4 men band. After Marius Nedelcu left the band in April 2008 to pursue a solo career, the three remaining boys called in Corneliu Ulici, a former member of Romanian group "Bliss". However, in September 2009, after only 9 months, Corneliu left the band to dedicate his time to his acting career. On 4 September 2013 the group split up. Adrian took into account the group's name. The other two members went to form a duo, "TWO".

name: Adrian Sina
comments: Dance DJ, songwriter & producer, started as DJ in a club at 16, ran his own radio show at 18. Produced some songs on the first album of Akcent, Romanian band he has been a member of ever since. In 2008, Adrian opened his own recording studio "SisterHoodLive Records", composing and producing Akcent's album "Fara Lacrimi" ("No Tears"). In 2009 he takes his career a step further with two new projects "Roller Sis" and "Vivien O'Hara". 2010 brought a new Sina hit, this time a collaboration with Andreea Banica, "Love in Brasil". This has also been the year that Adrian became a complete artist, launching his first solo project.

name: Ina Duncan
comments: Singer and dancer who appeared on Broadway and in film. William Sherwood Fox, President of the University of Western Ontario, wrote about her in his autobiography, "Sherwood Fox of Western." Fox was at Princeton (1911-1917) when he hired young Ina Duncan as his family cook. He described her singing songs from musical comedies and arias from operas as she did her work. He also noted that she was was knowledgeable and a good critic of paintings and sculpture. However, about a year after he hired her, she was arrested and taken to a prison for shooting a man. When he attempted to arrange her release, Fox was told by the District Attorney: "Mr. Fox, this is not the common kind of case I thought it was. The warden and his whole staff will be sorry to see Ina leave the jail. In two weeks she has changed the tone and spirit of the entire prison population, In the kitchen she has made the limited plain foodstuffs into tasty dishes which the prisoners relish. Then after the noonday meal and supper she sings to them the kind of popular song they like and tops them off now and then with a tuneful aria from an opera. After that - would you believe it? - she reads stories from the Atlantic and Harper's, and makes them like it. She has mesmerized the whole gang of them." The case was dismissed with Ina Duncan released on probation for a year.
